{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"6990f455-01cb-4608-b042-5926d67084cd","content":"Two things change with xUnit v3 + MTP:\n\n### 1. Filter syntax\nMTP replaces VSTest's `--filter` with `--filter-expression`. The operators change too:\n\n| VSTest (`--filter`) | MTP (`--filter-expression`) |\n|---|---|\n| `FullyQualifiedName~X` | `/**/X*` (glob on FQN) |\n| `Category=Smoke` | `Category=Smoke` (traits stay the same) |\n| `&` (AND) | `and` |\n\n### 2. Your new CI command\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter-expression \"/**/IntegrationTests* and Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\nOr if you invoke the test executable directly (common with MTP):\n\n```bash\ndotnet run -- --filter-expression \"/**/IntegrationTests* and Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\n### 3. `[Trait]` → xUnit v3 note\n\nYour `[Trait(\"Category\", \"Smoke\")]` still works in v3, but there's now a simpler built-in attribute:\n\n```csharp\n[Category(\"Smoke\")]   // xUnit v3 shorthand for [Trait(\"Category\", \"Smoke\")]\n```\n\nBoth are recognized by the same `Category=Smoke` filter expression — this is optional.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"08826d70-1525-440f-ab4a-a7c7691efe9d","outputTokens":312},"id":"1aefbd8e-171e-42ab-9eb0-cacc625ef67d","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:48:15.848Z","parentId":"48acae66-1b40-4b9b-9ff8-7e3df8742619"}
